      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To calculate optimal order quantities, we can use the Economic Order Quantity (EOQ) formula: EOQ = √(2DS), where D is demand and S is the lead time.\n\nFor SKU-9928 (Organic Almond Milk), assume D = 500 units/month and lead time S = 2 weeks = 14 days. \nEOQ = √(2*500*14) = √14000 ≈ 118 units.\n\nFor SKU-4410 (Whole Grain Bread), assume D = 300 units/month and lead time S = 3 weeks = 21 days. \nEOQ = √(2*300*21) = √12600 ≈ 112 units.\n\nFor SKU-1102 (Avocado Oil), assume D = 200 units/month and lead time S = 4 weeks = 28 days. \nEOQ = √(2*200*28) = √11200 ≈ 105 units.\n\nThese quantities should ensure a 0% stockout rate for each SKU.",
